Harry N. Abrams/Pocket Books | 1953 | ISBN: N/A | English | 94 pages | PDF | 12 MB

The charms of the French landscape, the holiday mood of Paris boulevards, cafes, and parks, and above all, the poetry of lightÃ¢â‚¬â€these are the subjects immortalized by the Impressionists in one of the most exciting art movements of the nineteenth century. Yet, when Monet, Renoir, Pissarro, and their associates first exhibited in 1874, their novel subjects and technique were greeted with jeers, and the name Impressionist was applied in ridicule. Now, the name has become honorable, just as their brilliant canvases have become perhaps the most widely loved in history
